main event: A round white object resembling a flame-out of an aircraft was observed through ground radar on 15 Aug 1961.
interesting points: The object appeared to resemble characteristics of an artificial satellite, The observation lasted for approximately 5 minutes, The object was moving at a high altitude, The course of the object was undetermined at the time of the sighting, The report was submitted through the Project Blue Book's investigation process.
witness description: 2nd Lieutenant Richard A. Kahane, Intelligence Officer, with experience of 2,332 flight hours.
